  <p class="en" style="font-size:12px;color:#52525b;margin-top:24px">Sources: Glassnode Docs, "SOPR (Spent Output Profit Ratio)" and "LTH-SOPR" concept and formula documentation (including the acknowledgment that large transfers in thinner, low-liquidity markets can skew SOPR); Glassnode's "Introducing Live SOPR" announcement (2019); Glassnode's "Breaking up On-Chain Metrics for Short and Long Term Investors" analysis (citing LTH-SOPR at or below 0.6 as a macro-bottom condition); historical Bitcoin price data for 2018–2020 and 2022 (public exchange records); public reporting on the Terra/Luna collapse (May 2022), Celsius halting withdrawals (June 12, 2022) and filing for bankruptcy (July 13, 2022), and the FTX collapse (November 2022).</p>
